    "approach": "The authors analyzed data from large-scale open source repositories to study how different branching patterns correlate with integration frequency and development outcomes.",
    "key_insights": [
      "Frequent branching helps isolate work but can delay integration if branches are long-lived.",
      "Short-lived branches encourage cohesion and reduce merge complexity.",
      "Teams benefit from balancing isolation and rapid integration depending on project context."
    ],
    "implications": "Understanding branching tradeoffs can help software teams adopt practices that improve collaboration efficiency and reduce integration costs."
  }
}
```

